The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Feb. 8 (PTI): Industrialist Mukesh Ambani today met CPM general secretary Prakash Karat to discuss economic issues, party sources said.          
	The meeting comes ahead of the budget session, scheduled to begin on Thursday, and amid indications of a fractured verdict in the Lok Sabha election.                   
	 Phagwara (PTI): Two robbers in police uniform hijacked a car at gunpoint outside a hospital in Hoshiarpur, Punjab, on Saturday. Daljit Singh had come to meet an ailing uncle and was lying on the seat of his Tata Safari when he was attacked. Singh was later bundled out at a village with his hands and legs tied. The robbers escaped with the car.                   
	 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): The Dar-ul Uloom has issued a decree declaring the BSP slogan Jai Bhim un-Islamic. The fatwa said the slogan, invoking Bhimrao Ambedkar, was against the Islamic law as the religion does not permit such a prayer for anyone except Allah.                  
	 Toronto (PTI): An Indian-origin man has been charged with drugging and sexually assaulting a woman at a nightclub. Jagdeep Chahal, 32, surrendered to police on Saturday after the woman complained she was assaulted in the bathroom of the club after a drug was slipped into her drink on January 22.                  
	 London (PTI): The mother of Scarlett Keeling, the British teenager murdered near a Goa beach last year, has passed on to the CBI the emails sent by her daughter to a Spanish friend a few days before her death. Fiona MacKeown was quoted as saying the emails made her question her decision to leave Scarlett behind in Goa while the rest of the family travelled down the Indian coast.                  
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): A six-year old girl was killed by a leopard in Uttarakhands Chamoli district on Saturday. Suman was dragged away by the animal to a nearby jungle. Villagers later found her half-eaten body.                                                                                                                           
